storyInfo: Amiya and the Doctor blow up the defense artillery control room atop the wall. Siege starts up a Royal Family escape route below, leading the Self-Salvation Corps free of the Sanguinarch's grasp. En route on their evacuation, Amiya sees Theresa in the ruins.

attributes.content: You're already down to your last few men.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: On any past battlefield, Victoria would've needed at least two or more Steam Knights in order to hold me off.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: But look at yourselves now—
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: You're just a bunch of plain soldiers.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: —Hold formation!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Those who still have energy in your shields! Stand together with me!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Snipers, sustain fire, pin him!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Yes, Captain!
attributes.name: Robben

attributes.content: I've said it before—no matter how strong he is, he's still just a flesh-and-blood Sarkaz Infected. His Arts have a limit!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You want to wait until I cast my body dry?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: You'll never live to see me exhaust my strength.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Ugh!
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: Blake!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Horn, take my sword—
attributes.name: Victorian Soldier

attributes.content: —Got it.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: When they fall, they turn their gazes to you, still with hope.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: I never thought I'd see such brilliance in Londinium again.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: But how much longer can this fragile light persist?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Horn!
attributes.name: Robben

attributes.content: ...Robben?
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: *pant*... *pant*... No cause for alarm... falling here... just returning... returning... back to Londinium's land.
attributes.name: Robben

attributes.content: Sarkaz!!!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You fired all of your remaining ammunition at once?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Well done. You've stopped me in my tracks for the first time.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: But after this, you're out of tricks.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: After you watch your comrades die one by one, will you lose the will to fight too, White Wolf?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.text: Rita.
I can understand how disappointed you are in your father.
Yes, a soldier's blood flows through my body.
But just as Victoria invented steam trains, yet only decades later abandoned steam—
Modern Victoria has taken off the crown meant for people to lift their gazes at, and no longer needs soldiers like your great-grandmother or me to fight for her.
There'll come a day the White Wolf, together with the Lion Padishah he accompanied, will be no more than indistinct images left in the history books.
Your father's taken note of that. He's ground down his own sharp claws so the family isn't torn apart by the tides of the ages.
But you're different.
You grow in a changing Victoria.
Rita Skamandros, you won't need to fight a landtrotter's campaign in the name of the Aslan King.
But Victoria is still your home.

attributes.content: Sarkaz... So long as you occupy our cities, I will always have a reason to fight.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: My desire to defeat you is shared with every Victorian.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Your shield is of little use now.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: I still have a sword.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Your sword... heh, common as could be.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: You want to battle me with a sword like this?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: *huff*... Don't underestimate it, or me.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You're so fond of remembering... the Steam Knights...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: When you take off the armor that Victoria forged them...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: They turn out just to be—
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Victorians!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: We actually... got inside? Why has this wall turned so soft?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Not bad! For an instant back there, I thought I was gonna get my head painted over Londinium's walls!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: It was Misery's Arts. He wouldn't see us hurt.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Right... Kal'tsit told me your brain was an important asset to Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: My hands don't come cheap either, c'mon!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: After that, I'm never asking to hitchhike with you again... Blaze carrying me everywhere is a way smoother ride than your Arts!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Am I right or am I right, Doctor?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.options: Your hands are always busy. That's gotta be something.;I wouldn't say the Blaze Express is THAT comfortable.
You'd better take a breather, Misery.

attributes.content: I agree. Misery, I saw it clearly... Manfred almost impaled you with that thrust.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: That was just a desperation blow. He had no other move.
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: You successfully provoked his rage, and that made him overlook my approach. I didn't even think I could fool him twice.
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: I didn't at all intend to...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: When he asked me that, I definitely felt his anger. That rage of his rushed at me like a heatwave.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: If Manfred uses all his strength, anyone nearby would have trouble lasting for long. Best I... *cough* *cough* *cough*...
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: Misery, I know you want to help that Victorian officer, but using large-scale matter-transformation Arts several times in one day is too taxing on your body.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: It's okay, Amiya.
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: I won't drop dead for a while yet. Besides, I promised Kal'tsit...
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: You elite operators... make plenty of promises to Dr. Kal'tsit, don't you?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Inject these emergency meds into yourself. The fight in Londinium's only just begun, and I don't want to see you off somewhere alone again, swallowing down all the blood you're practically throwing up.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Amiya, enemies inbound.
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.options: Feist, tie up six ziplines to me.

attributes.content: Hm. Misery found us a weak point in Londinium's defense system... We need to see this control room destroyed.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Blistering speed—White Wolf, this was your true aim, wasn't it?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Fangs and claws as fierce as these, yet tamed by Victoria's noble etiquette... Was it really worth it?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Sarkaz, wasn't your present appearance once packaged in so-called culture?
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: I hear your people used to look very different.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You can try your hardest, but you still cannot kill me. So long as this city's defenses continue to churn—
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: No. Wait. White Wolf, you're only stalling me!
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: You—You and Rhodes Island are collaborating again.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Do you know who they are? Do you know what that Cautus leader...?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: I only know—that they can stop you.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: White Wolf, should you miraculously succeed today... you will witness a corner of Londinium's walls collapse, with your own eyes.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Is that what you want to see? From this moment on, the legend of Londinium everstanding may well no longer—
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: From this moment on?
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: The fact you can be stood here means... the idea that Londinium has never fallen is nothing more than a self-reassuring joke.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Damn you! If those dukes outside take note of this—
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Are you aware? You're finally showing a hint of panic in your face.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: That goes to show my decision was the correct one.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: If this wall... only exists to smother the screams of the Victorians from within, then it's already lost its founding purpose.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You ought to let those dukes hear!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Hear... how our fellow citizens cry out under your slaughter!
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: How... How much longer until we can go outside?
attributes.name: Londinium Citizen

attributes.content: Oh... it feels like this passage is about to collapse... are we all going to die here?
attributes.name: Londinium Citizen

attributes.content: Don't look down, and don't look back.
attributes.name: Heidi

attributes.content: If the fear gets too much, just stare at the way ahead.
attributes.name: Heidi

attributes.content: The signal light's still on. This is our hope that our soldiers lit for us.
attributes.name: Heidi

attributes.content: We wait for the light as it turns bright... and then we can catch sight of the sun in Londinium once again.
attributes.name: Heidi

attributes.content: Their firepower's too strong—
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: Rockrock, we can't get any closer to the train.
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: The bombardment hasn't stopped... Can the people down below still hold out? How much time do we have left?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: There's been no word from the commander's end...
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: I... I believe in my family.
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: That's the one and only reason I've kept on this far.
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: Bloody hell, I can't get these things off me!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: That's not it... You saw how fast they were a moment ago?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: He's slowing them on purpose, like he's... just watching how long we can run for...
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: What kind of sicko is he?
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Mmm... listen to the sound of your breaths, your pulses. Are you finally tired out?
Is this... the honor of the Sarkaz?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: This isn't fit to be called a battle.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: ...Battle?
You seem to have the wrong idea.
The 'King of Sarkaz' isn't here, so I'm left with no matching opponent at all.

Would you converse with a meatbeast about glory or honor? When you know full well that hunting them serves to do nothing but excite your senses, that their only ultimate service is as an entrée on your dinner table?
You treat us... as prey?
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: You may be a Sarkaz, but slaughtering like this out of pure personal taste is still far too barbaric.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Do not appraise me by your understanding of culture. It would be the most hideous kind of slander to me.
Try and resist me, before the filthy rubble pummels you into mincemeat here.
I will borrow your blood to record your feelings at death's door... all your fear, unwillingness, anger... Let them burst forth upon me to your heart's content!
Vina, get over here—
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: No.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Vina!
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Morgan, you fall back too.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Urgh...
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: You're going to stand in front of all of us, and resist him?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Yes.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: You're no match for him.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: And you're not planning to turn and flee, even if you'll be shredded in an instant, have your flesh leave the dullest stain in this whole tunnel?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Only if... you can all run faster than I can.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Why?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Because...
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: There is no because. I just want to do this.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: When the city above us falls towards us, I want to be the first to embrace it in that instant.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: If that's so...
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: The signal light in the passage seems to glow brighter.
Are her eyes failing her? Why is there starlight in Londinium's underground? No... how long have they gone without seeing the stars behind the clouds, even on the surface?
Siege blinks.
She suddenly realizes that is no star.
It is a button.
The detritus that caked it has been shaken off, and now it is shining, and she has the exact fortune to know what it does.
She was first brought underneath the palace at three years of age.
Her mentor carried her upon his back, using a tremendous paw to guide her in pushing this button.
Londinium's subterranean sprawled about its own muscle and bone, exposing to the future liege its veins and arteries, filled with life.
Over twenty years later—
She has found it for the second time.
Bombs mounted at all nodes!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: Doctor, I've got our retreat ready!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Move it, they're in here, stop them—
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Urgh...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Amiya! Dammit, how are they coming so thick and fast... did Misery leave too late? Did they not stall Manfred?
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: I'll hold them off! All of you, go!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Doctor, give the detonator to me—
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: You won't have a chance to retreat unless I lock down these enemies!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Once you've successfully withdrawn, I'll blow up this control room straight away—
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Doctor, we can't wait any longer! Think of the Self-Salvation Corps' fighters, Victoria's soldiers, Lady Heidi and Siege's team...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: And every single Victorian being bombarded right now! None of us can hold on anymore!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.options: Tell me—when to push the detonator.

attributes.content: Doctor...!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: *cough* *cough*... These black lines are everywhere... I can't see anything!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Now!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Doctor, why are you... in front of me?
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.text: Because I want to be.

attributes.content: I'm not... not the weak child I was anymore...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: I won't drag you down anymore. I can withstand these Arts, and these flames.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.text: I know.
You're so powerful now. Far more powerful than I am, probably.
But no matter how many opportunities you give me to choose...
No matter if we're confronted with a Draco's flames, or the fiery light of these explosions...
This is what I want to do.

attributes.content: Doctor...
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Oof... caught you!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Wondered why you asked me for those six ziplines, Doctor. This is what it was for?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: It'll be hard to move about, but... oh well, not as if you run fast ordinarily...
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Fly, my drones!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: How's that for a surprise, Doctor? In response to your demands, I've tinkered on my drones and finally developed—a people-towing glider function!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: There's a cap on its long-term use, but at least it'll get us safely on the ground—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.options: Now's the time to dial up the explosions.

attributes.content: The control room—!
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: They... did it...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Urgh...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: How... How long ago did you tire out? You can't even brandish your sword now...
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: You really were doing nothing but... making a stand with all you had.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Anyone else with your wounds would be in a coma ten times over by now!
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Now you realize? Slow, aren't you.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: General, the explosion in the control room has affected the cannons. The batteries and the minor section of the wall structure here have all been severely damaged—
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: If we hang around here any longer, we'll fall!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Notify all hands, retreat!
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: What about this soldier?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: I've defeated her already, but toppling her would require spending more effort still.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: And it's not worth spending the time here any longer.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Ha... haha...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: White Wolf of Victoria, you are a worthy opponent.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Should you live to descend this city wall—
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Then next time we meet, by my sword... I will send you to a death befittingly heroic.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Next time...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Will there be a next time?
Londinium's wall is falling down.
And so she endlessly falls too.
I... I did it.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Until... you all left...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: ...I did not fall.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Her blood flows out, and she almost loses the last speck of awareness she has.
But her body is as if a part of her sword and shield at this point, harder than steel, unbending unless shattered.
The weapon forged by Victoria still stands upon Londinium's wall.
So the soldier She tempered to fruition keeps her watch upon it too.
Until a corner of it crashes to its city's ground—
And she returns to the land that raised her.
Just how tall... is this wall?
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Why is it like...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: ...I'm flying up?
Horn, can you still move? Grab my hand, quick!
...Robben?
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: You're... not...
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Yes, I'm not dead! I was lucky enough to grab onto the outside structure when I fell, and then Mr. Misery here saved me again!
attributes.name: Robben

attributes.content: Come, soldier. You haven't finished your fight yet.
attributes.name: Misery

attributes.content: You lot, honestly. You won't ever let me rest, will you?
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Nope!
attributes.name: Robben

attributes.content: Horn, don't shut your eyes! Don't forget, your soldier is still here! You can't fall!
attributes.name: Robben

attributes.content: Robben, you've turned as noisy as... as a certain someone, now.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Oh, forget it... I've never been able to do anything about you lot.
attributes.name: Horn

attributes.content: Her vision becomes clear once again.
The city wall of Londinium is still there, and though its highest height is now adorned by the tiniest hole, it still seems as towering, as unyielding as ever.
What's that shaking?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Artillery finally do the underground structure in?
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: No, that's not it.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: This shaking's coming from underneath us—
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Vina, what did you do?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: I've found a path we can walk.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Is this whole tunnel... moving up?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: How? You'd think we'd know it could do that after living here for so long, right?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: There are always some 'locals' who'll know more than others.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: That monster...
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Is it still gonna come after?
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: It will.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: But maybe not today.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: So you found a new course to flee down?
Ah... but of course, but of course.
This scent... is it that Feline, giving it off?
No... so-called royal families are no more than a lie, so called to consolidate power and coin, as laughable as this nation's culture.
Even if she is that runaway's cub, the smell of her blood would be no different to any other Feline.
So, this completely different scent...
Interesting.
Does Theresis know about this?
You'll have no chance to verify for yourself.
Oh?
I remember who you are. You're that... little disciple by Theresis's side. Even if your teacher was stood right here, he would be troubled to apprehend me.
He's no longer fit to be my teacher anymore.
Hm?
This odor of cursecraft... So you've come too, Banshee? I'd thought you were in that city right now, playing games with my entourage.
Trifling, unpracticed Artists. They weren't enough to hinder my step.
*sigh*... That makes things tricky.
This underpass on the verge of collapse is no fine place for the Royal Court to congregate.
Am I nothing in his eyes? Just because I didn't learn my skills from Theresis, or have any noble blood?
This long-winded old man's genuinely pissed me off. I'm going to gift him a hundred bombs as a farewell present. Any of you have any objections?
...Report.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Rhodes Island's people have jumped out from the control room. They had that Cautus, so we couldn't snipe them—
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: And the rebels in the underground tunnels?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Er, we detected an explosion from beneath... and the Sanguinarch hasn't returned yet.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Where is Hoederer?
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: He's severely wounded, and currently unconscious.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Assemble what workers remain, and have them inspect the city defense systems and report the damages. We must be prepared to activate more batteries... and even the main cannons.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Surround the remaining individuals at the station. The surviving rebels will be sure to pass through there.
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: The... The scouts are reporting, they've detected another group rapidly closing in on the station—
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Manfred, don't blame yourself too much. You've already tried your hardest.
What are you doing here—
attributes.name: Manfred

attributes.content: Rockrock, take a look at the city wall—
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: The defense artillery's been... shut down?
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: Send the signal!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: They're coming, they're all coming!
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: But the Sarkaz... they're all rushing this way!
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: Stop them! Kill every last one!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: If we can just repel the Sarkaz, we can start up the train!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: You're not getting away that easily!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Ugh—
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: How's the rebel army coming from that way too?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Warrior

attributes.content: Is that reinforcements?
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: A team's broken through the Sarkaz forces' blockade from the north side!
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: Who... Who called them in?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: Did some of the Messengers we sent to the city center survive? Did they get to ask for help?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: You've done a fine job, my Sudean friends!
attributes.name: Victorian Mercenary

attributes.content: You can leave the next battle to us now! We're more on the professional end!
attributes.name: Victorian Mercenary

attributes.content: The way they work... they must have loads of experience...
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: Is... Is that Rhodes Island's operator?
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: Break them up!
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Make a passage, ensure the Self-Salvation fighters withdraw from the underpass safely!
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Snipers, take down those signalers—
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: It's—Miss Montague!
attributes.name: Victorian Mercenary

attributes.content: Montague?
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: That name rings a bell and a half! Some noble in the paper or something?
attributes.name: Self-Salvation Corps Soldier

attributes.content: Don't get distracted!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: No matter who they are, we're on the same side!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: We can get through! Quick, lead everyone onto the train!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: Oh, wow... Lady Heidi, we've made it...
attributes.name: Londinium Citizen

attributes.content: Mm-hm, I told you. Our soldiers won't let us down.
attributes.name: Heidi

attributes.content: They're her people.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Did our Messengers get in contact with her?
attributes.name: Heidi

attributes.content: To be more precise, it was your Rhodes Island Messenger.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Dagda! Look, it's Dagda!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: That tart...
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Hm.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: There among the crowd, Dagda sees them too.
She throws down the Sarkaz she's tussling with, and rushes through the passage made with no hesitation, arms reached out to her partners caked in grime.
I... I was so scared I'd be late.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: No, you weren't.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: No matter when you come back, we could never call you late.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Bastard, you... you stormed off just like that, remember? I didn't even get to beat you up!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: Hm... you're still in time to do it now.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Ay, Vina, did you know she'd come back?
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: I knew.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: I get you hid it from Indra. She'd never take help from nobles' mercenaries unless it was critical as this, end-of-the-line type.
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Stop griping about me and let's get these idiots dealt with first!
attributes.name: Indra

attributes.content: I never stopped here!
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: Vina, I didn't finish... you could've at least given me a shout!
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: *sigh* You had me wondering if Dagda was off in some corner again even while we were being killed! I was all ready to take the Sarkaz down with me!
attributes.name: Morgan

attributes.content: I'm sorry, Morgan...
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: This won't happen again. I swear.
attributes.name: Dagda

attributes.content: Siege Group, fully assembled.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: We just wait for the Doctor's lot to come back, and we can all get out of here together.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Everyone, we're back!
Amiya?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Fancy coming in from the sky, all of you...
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: We're touching down! Gangway, outta the way—
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: G—Grab the zipline! Don't crash into the train, it's our only means of escaping alive!
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: I've got the Doctor held, we're alright!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Safe landing!
attributes.name: Closure

attributes.content: We... We actually made it?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Rockrock—
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: Commander, is Rockrock alright? Everyone evacuated out?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: We have more survivors than anticipated.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: It's thanks to you, Feist, and everyone you brought in from Rhodes Island.
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Hah... You see that, Old Bill?
attributes.name: Feist

attributes.content: No, don't you faint on the job now! The battle's still not done!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: If you can move, then come help me in the engine room!
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: There are still Sarkaz forces pursuing us.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: There's nothing they can do, now.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Because we'll hold them off here.
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Right, damned right.
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Commander, the train's setting off—
attributes.name: Rockrock

attributes.content: All ready?
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.content: Amiya, we're getting on!
attributes.name: Siege

attributes.content: Alright!
attributes.name: Amiya

attributes.content: Go!
attributes.name: Clovisia

attributes.text: Amiya?
Amiya, careful. The train's moving.
Amiya... what are you looking at?

attributes.content: The Cautus girl does not reply to you. Her body is still. Even her breathing seems to have stopped.
You can tell she's shocked. She's never let emotions as unveiled and intense show before the operators. This moment is incomparable.
At the same time, the Sarkaz chasing the train all come to a halt.
They all turn their heads, looking in the same direction.
A Sarkaz enters the ruins.
All smoke seems to part at her feet, all sounds of fire suspended about her.
Only wind remains, growing stronger and fiercer.
The ash laden on the ground is blown about, some sticking to her attire, some smudging her pale hair. She seems not to mind at all, only silently gazing into a point of the ruins.
It seems to have once been part of the defense artillery. A jet-black fowlbeast is there now, perched atop the still-warm cannon mouth.
Most likely disturbed by the train picking up in speed, it shakes off its wings.
As if somewhat in response, the pale-haired Sarkaz turns around.
She should have no sight of who is aboard the train, but her expression is as if she has recognized who is looking at her.
Her face is so warm, yet her eyes are so filled with sorrow. The sorrow is so much; perhaps not all of it comes from her, but comes from the one who stares at her too.

attributes.text: Amiya, are you alright?

attributes.content: The Cautus girl finally comes back to reality.
She still doesn't give you a response, and you're in no rush for her to give one.
In one ear, you hear the calls of fowlbeasts. You see a flock of them out of the window flapping through the air, rushing into the gale ahead of you.
The train takes you rapidly from the station.
The city wall, the war, and that pale-haired figure, all are left far, far behind you.
Rumble. Rumble. Rumble.
Is that the remnants of cannon fire lingering in your brain, the train bumping against the railway, or thunder in those gloomy clouds gathering not far away?
The center of Londinium is right before you.
And all of you are riding into this storm.
